<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8430719>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–12. (1–4). Maladera kolkataensis Bhunia, Gupta, Sarkar &Ahrens, new species (holotype); (5–8). Gynaecoserica perdita Ahrens, 2004 (Kurseong, West Bengal); (9–12). Maladera affinis (Blanchard, 1850) (Purnea, Bihar); (1, 5, 8) Aedeagus in lateral view (left); (2,6, 10) Aedeagus in dorsal view; (3, 7, 11) Aedeagus in lateral view (right); (4, 8, 12) Habitus, dorsal view. Scale 0.5 mm. Habitus not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8430719/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8430745>
    dc:description "FIGURE 98. (A–B). A. Gangetic plains biogeographic zone of India; B. Map of Lower Gangetic plains showing sample localities of the species: Maladera kolkataensis, Gynaecoserica perdita, Maladera affinis, M. allopruinosa, M. bengalensi, M. burmeisteri burmeisteri, M. cardoni." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8430745/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

